notesStmt.note: This manuscript is an anonymous illuminated and illustrated tenth-century AH / sixteenth CE copy of the Collection of poems (dīvān) by Ḥāfiẓ (fl. eighth century AH / fourteenth CE). Written in nastaʿlīq script, this codex opens with a double-page illuminated frontispiece and has three additional double-page illustrations.

msContents.textLang: The primary language in this manuscript is Persian. The secondary language of this manuscript is Arabic.

msItem.title: Dīvān-i Ḥāfiẓ
ديوان حافظ
msItem.incipit: الا يا ايها الساقى ادر كاسا وناولها...

colophon.note: tamma al-kitāb bi-ʿawn Allāh wa-ḥusn tawfīqih /1/ wa-al-ṣalāh wa-al-salām ʿalá khayr /2/ khalqih Muḥammad wa-ālih /3/ ajmaʿīn /4/
In Arabic; no name of scribe or date of copying

decoDesc.decoNote: Three double-page illustrations (fols. 39b-40a, 88b-89a, and 171b-172a; double-page illuminated frontispiece with oval medallions enclosing the title of the work and the first four couplets (fols. 1b-2a); small rectangular or triangular pieces with floral designs on the sides of selected verses; frame

decoNote.title: Double-page illuminated frontispiece with titlepiece
decoNote.note: This is the right side of a double-page illuminated frontispiece. It has the title of the work and the first four couplets inscribed in white nastaʿlīq script in the central oval medallion.

decoNote.title: Double-page illuminated frontispiece with titlepiece
decoNote.note: This is the left side of a double-page illuminated frontispiece. It has the title of the work and the first four couplets inscribed in white nastaʿlīq script in the central oval medallion.

decoNote.title: Double-page illustration
decoNote.note: This is the right side of a double-page illustration, depicting a mosque scene with a preacher and its congregation (both men and women).

decoNote.title: Double-page illustration
decoNote.note: This is the right side of a double-page illustration, depicting a tavern scene (perhaps in Shiraz) with jars of wine and musicians.

binding.p: Dark brown leather (with flap); central lobed medallion with pendants and cornerpieces brushed with gold; endleaves of marbled paper; gilt edges

history.provenance: Seal impression: Muḥammad Rizā Javāhid Zamūnī[?] (fol. 1a)
